Sentencas: The formation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) nanoparticles on cathode surfaces enhances the charge conductivity, thus enabling high performance in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the 0D structure has limitations such as inefficient charge conducting paths and fading of reaction sites due to the excessive loading level needed to ensure continuity of the nanoparticles.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, we report a uniformly grown ultrathin 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta nanosheet that can be used to enhance cathode performance.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The continuous 2D form more efficiently enlarges the reaction site and has a low loading level compared to the conventional 0D form.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 2D nanosheet structure is ideal for enlarging the charge conducting path because it shows favorable networking within the cathode scaffold compared to other structures.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A solid oxide fuel cell using a 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta nanosheet exhibits an enhanced power density of 1.2 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This improvement occurs because the nanosheet facilitates charge conducting within the cathode.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our strategy provides a method to build high-performance solid oxide fuel cells using a cathode structure design.
Titulo: Subcontinuous 2D La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ nanosheet as an efficient charge conductor for boosting the cathodic activity of solid oxide fuel cells
